text.Taxonomy and naming-Subspecies:
The following subspecies have been described by Robert Chinnock:
Eremophila pterocarpa subsp. pterocarpa which has leaves that are flat and 2–5.6 millimetres (0.08–0.2 in) wide;
Eremophila pterocarpa subsp. acicularis which has leaves that are needle-like or linear in shape, 1–2 millimetres (0.04–0.08 in) wide and have a channel along their lower surface.
